      <hedline>
        <hl1>Guzzling Gas As the Cost Rises</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Assembly Speaker Sheldon Silver letter on August 13 editorial on loophole in New York State's campaign finance laws that allows corporations to surpass contributions limits to candidates by forming subsidiaries</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As our country continues to participate, with no end in sight, in a war that some believe is at least partly based on our country's unquenchable thirst for oil, it pains me to read stories of young men and women who seem to have little regard for the conservation of fossil fuels (''Young Drivers Squeeze Out the Miles,'' Aug. 13).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As our country continues to participate, with no end in sight, in a war that some believe is at least partly based on our country's unquenchable thirst for oil, it pains me to read stories of young men and women who seem to have little regard for the conservation of fossil fuels (''Young Drivers Squeeze Out the Miles,'' Aug. 13).</p>
        <p>While Sean Szabunka, the 19-year-old who switched cars so that he could continue to drive 300 to 400 miles a week ''just for fun,'' continues to indulge his passion, I can't help thinking about other 19-year-old men and women who are on the other side of the world losing their lives and limbs just so that Mr. Szabunka can indulge his passion. Does he ever think about them?</p>
        <p>Lorraine Mesagna  Manhasset</p>
      </block>
